abstract: >
  Ouroboros Thesis v22 (Convergence) consolidates the May-June 2026 formal-verification
  advances into the canonical thesis line. A5 permutation invariance is added as a structure
  field (not a new axiom; unique-axiom count stays 14), correcting the false A1-A4 uniqueness
  claim with a verified counterexample. The n-dimensional Cauchy functional-equation chain is
  partially closed (topology, functional-analysis, symmetric branches in review). VCG mechanism
  truthfulness is proven on branch; SLSA L2 build provenance is attested on 5/5 GHCR images
  (L1 + L2, not L3); Innovation Rounds 10-11 add frontier physics, quantum, CS, and crypto
  formalizations; and a Sim-to-Real doctrine-transfer benchmark modeled on the Walrus physical
  foundation model measures a mean doctrine alpha-gap of 0.10 across five unseen compliance
  regimes. The Lambda-aggregator remains Conjecture 1 - NOT a theorem. Doctrine v11 LOCKED
  749/14/163 at kernel commit c7c0ba17 (v11.1 in flight post-A5: 794/14/191). Concept DOI:
  10.5281/zenodo.19944926; the v22 version DOI is minted by Zenodo on the paper-v22-1.0.0 release.
keywords:
  - AI governance
  - Ouroboros
